With this sentence, the managing director of Telecinco, Paolo Vasile, announced his satisfaction at the close of the stock market. The channel he managed had increased its value by twice that of its rival Antena 3.
One aspect, however, dampened his joy: “That&#39;s exactly what hurt me; not that we had higher growth, but that we had lower losses,” he noted.
He stressed that despite the weak market, &quot;they haven&#39;t sunk too low.&quot;
Telecinco ended the day up 2.54% yesterday.
This gain cuts his losses so far this year to 15.66%.
According to Bloomberg data, the goodwill now reaches 4,488.88 million euros, with Mediaset controlling the majority of the capital (52%) and Vocento owning only 13%.
Rival Antena 3 lost 1.52 percentage points yesterday and is down 40.5% since January, halving its market value at 2,193.46 million.
The market value of other listed communication companies, on the other hand, is increasing; 3,571 million for Sogecable, 2,518.53 million for Prisa (editor of the magazine Cinco Días) and 1,779 million for Vocento.
The comparison with Antena 3 can be derived from the fact that &quot;they are two similar companies&quot;, according to Vasile.
The question of the extent to which we can actually act on the stock exchange, at what price and how we can make it lucrative at customer level still seems uncertain.
Telecinco announced a week ago that it intends to become the first TV station with more than 1,000 million gross profits from advertising this year. This was assured by Guiseppe Tringali, the managing director of Telecinco and Publiespaña, the group&#39;s advertising company.
If implemented, the channel would increase its advertising revenues by 3.6% compared to 965.4 million in the previous year.
In the case of Antena 3, net sales increased by 1.6% in the first nine months of trading (up to 734.4 million), while net income from the television business increased by only 0.7% (630.4 million). could have.
The analysts see the main factor for Telecinco&#39;s comparatively better stock market development in the high payout ratio that the company has been able to show up to now: In 2006, the company managed by Alejandro Echevarría arranged for a 100 percent dividend payout.
However, Vasile assures that the ratio could still vary after the purchase of 33% of Endemol&#39;s shares, with Mediaset as parent company, although it is too early for an official announcement.
“We are committed to the official compromise of paying out at least 50% of the shares, even though we have always stated significantly more.
I hope that this year we can satisfy our shareholders, whose share values we have already increased by buying 33% of Endemol&#39;s shares.
According to the analysts, the market is currently showing certain downward trend.
Lehmann Brothers recently reduced its profit estimate at Telecinco by 4% for this year and 7% for 2009.
This is the consequence of the cut in the projected growth rate, which will fall from 10.5% to 8.4% in 2008 and from 5.5% to 5.1% in 2009.
This has also lowered Antena 3&#39;s expected profit calculation for 2008 by 4.5% and for 2009 by 7.5%.
3 options.
