Ibersecurities: relies on its high effective yield and its sustainable potential and therefore recommends buying both stocks.
2.
Caja Madrid: attributes Telecinco (buy) to a more advantageous position than Antena 3 (hold) as a result of the “multiple incentives” and the prospering market.
3.
JPMorgan: recommends lowering expectations in both cases given the &quot;similar threats&quot; (saturated market and worsening economic climate).
Congress approves MIFID policy, which came into effect on November 1st.
In parallel with the parliamentary elaboration, which ended today with the Senate Congress decision on the amendments/amendments related to the project, the government published the provisions resulting from the new law with the intention of extending the entry into force of both regulations by the end of May allow year.
The representatives of the various companies unanimously commended the efforts of the Congress and Senate deputies, who, in their negotiations and votes, pursued the goal of establishing the best possible regulation, which ensures the security of investors and regulates the individual entrepreneurial activities, in order to achieve a generally efficient to guarantee market activity.
In addition to modernizing the financial markets, the MIFID, which redefines the Securities Services Ordinance, aims to improve investor protection, increase the control entitlement of the Spanish Securities Commission (CNMV) and promote cooperation between the various control authorities in the European Union.
The new directive makes it possible to offer financial advice both to specialized companies and to natural or legal persons, and also contributes to the creation of new financial services companies (ESIS), the advisory companies that merge with investment and brokerage companies of securities.
Moreover, it expands the number of systems for the execution of financial transactions, adding to the regulated circulating markets multilateral systems of securities trading and systems for the internationalization of trading orders, which would eventually compete with current economic players.
The law obliges investment companies to disclose the main features of their company profile, the exposure and forms of risk management on the market and to register all the projects carried out, thus facilitating the CNMV&#39;s task of control.
The Congressional Economic Commission subsequently envisaged other changes, with the US mortgage and banking crisis confirming that the titled debt should now be considered a &quot;complex&quot; financial instrument due to its high level of risk to the investor. (US Mortgage Crisis)
In addition, use was made of the entry into force of the directive to legally limit the work areas of qualified economists; 30 years after the 1977 decree limiting the work areas reserved for economists was issued.
For its part, the Senate established new positions in the financial sector, such as that of commercial mediator, who works on behalf of a third party, does not require authorization from the CNMV and can offer its services of commercializing products and client acquisition simultaneously to several investment companies.
The harmonized index of consumer prices (CPI) rose by five tenths in November and is now at 4.1%.
The indicator, which Eurostat uses to assess the inflation rate within the European Union, provides the average price development that took place in Spain in November.
Its publication corresponds to the principles of Eurostat and the European Central Bank (ECB), which aim to compare the location and quality of US products by publishing the data.
The forecast for the indicator can be prepared ahead of time using the same approach as for the harmonized index of consumer prices, but at the same time using various other statistical modeling methods to estimate the information that is not available at the time of calculation.
However, the Spanish statistical office (INE) warned that the prematurely determined indicator only serves as a guide and therefore does not have to agree with the final result, which will be announced next December 14th.
“The Consumer Price Index (CPI) will remain at a relatively high level”
According to Deputy Prime Minister and Economy and Finance Minister Pedro Solbes, November&#39;s rise in CPI was a &quot;temporary development&quot;; at the same time, he assured that the price index would remain at a &quot;relatively high&quot; level in the coming months.
Still, in the halls of the Congress building, Solbes noted that &quot;even if the current number isn&#39;t good,&quot; Spain&#39;s inflation differential with other members of the monetary union has &quot;more or less&quot; stayed the same in recent years.
He also explained that November &quot;had fewer surprises&quot; than the previous month, when the government was not expecting such a large increase.
&quot;We expected a value of around 4%,&quot; announced the Economy and Finance Minister with regard to the forecast published today.
