Which insurance is best for me?
Car insurance, which covers possible damage caused by the driver, entails a high cost, the amount of which in turn depends on various factors, including age, gender, when the driver&#39;s license was issued, marital status, the type of car to be insured and how it is used, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, you have to be clear about what we are dealing with here.
Auto insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and a policyholder.
This agreement is recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to submit the corresponding compensation sum in the event of a claim.
The insurance premium is the price of insurance, which is determined by a number of factors, including age, gender, date of issue of driver&#39;s license, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or how it is used.
The insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that higher premium payments are due if there is a higher risk of an accident.
As a result, both the over-25s and women pay less because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same also applies to married people, since, according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the conviction of the companies, they tend to have fewer accidents than single people.
The utility attributed to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, insurance companies have to take a number of points into account.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that best meets his personal needs.
At this point we list the most important points that you should consider when choosing an insurance policy, so that you can make a choice that is not only performance-based but also price-based.
The under 25-year-olds encounter numerous obstacles when choosing a low-cost insurance, such as little driving experience and the &quot;young&quot; driver&#39;s license.
Even if comprehensive insurance would be best for ideal insurance coverage, there are still cheaper alternatives.
Prudent drivers can choose Collision Damage Waiver with Excess, covering the benefits of Collision Damage Waiver but at a lower price.
This type of contract means that the customer has to pay part of the amount resulting from the damage himself.
“The amount is determined before the contract is concluded and based on the amount of the insurance premium. This is higher the lower the sum to be paid,” explains Luis Noguera, main representative for Spain at First Europa, a brokerage company for online insurance.
Another option is extended insurance, which insures customers against external accidental damage, but not against damage caused to their own car.
Also, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here&#39;s some advice.
If you&#39;re under 25, it&#39;s up to you to reduce insurance costs; this will increase your credit by trying to drive carefully and avoiding accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the base rate with the relevant insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in said tariff.
“The amount of credits and penalties depend on the company and its income.
If the company has had a profitable year, it can afford to increase the bonus payments,” explains Noguera.
Once the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract. The reason for this is the fact that the accident rate decreases with increasing driving practice.
Therefore, it makes the most sense to opt for fully comprehensive insurance with a deductible.
&quot;Usually, youngsters cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving&quot;, explains the Spanish director of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice, after the &quot;Beginner&#39;s Fear&quot; is discarded.
Nevertheless, for a married customer who has no children, it is more advisable to take out comprehensive insurance; Of course, only if the financial situation of the person in question allows it.
Insurers consider married couples with children to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and their premium payments are correspondingly low.
In this case, comprehensive insurance with a deductible (for an amount of around 300 euros) would be the best option. In the event that you have received a high credit, we recommend extended insurance, which only begins in the third year of the vehicle.
&quot;They drive more relaxed overall and have greater purchasing power, which allows them to charge higher premiums,&quot; notes Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it makes sense to take out fully comprehensive insurance with a deductible (for an amount of around 150 euros), or an extended insurance policy that only kicks in when the credit is sufficiently high.
Finally, it must be said that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver against possible accidental damage, but also because it involves high costs that require a thorough selection to be made that suits our personal situation .
