But the revelation that a wealthy businessman hid donations to Britain&#39;s ruling Labor Party of more than £650,000 ($1.3 million) over four years under other people&#39;s names, and that the party failed to report it, is something without which the embattled Gordon Brown would have gotten along well.
When two months ago the Prime Minister evaded calls for an election, stupidly insulting the intelligentsia of Britain by claiming that opinion polls had not influenced that decision, there was hope that he could provide a robust, efficient government would.
Instead, as Vince Cable, the increasingly astute Liberal Democrat branch chairman, put it, the once-dreaded Brown has evolved from Stalin into Mr. Bean.
