On the other hand, &quot;The Hunting Party&quot; is an exemplary way of investigating why there has actually never been a really good Balkan war film.
The story of three US war reporters who set out to track down the Serbian war criminal &quot;The Fox&quot; might have been a new &quot;Apocalypse Now&quot; with a different director and a different screenwriter (both in personal union Richard Shepard) at a different time can.
Because the stories are strikingly similar: Both times, small teams go into the forest to accomplish something that the military can&#39;t do, and both times it&#39;s a journey into madness.
One of the reasons for the failure of &quot;The Hunting Party&quot; is that they don&#39;t just let Simon Hunt be the down-and-out cynic with heart that he is introduced to us as at the beginning.
