After all, decades had to pass before Hollywood could make a good film about the Holocaust with &quot;Schindler&#39;s List&quot;.
Some films will probably still mature - the Vietnam works &quot;The Deer Hunter&quot;, &quot;Apocalypse Now&quot; or &quot;Full Metal Jackett&quot;, which are now considered classics, were by no means unanimously celebrated as masterpieces at the time.
But maybe today, when every mass murder comes in real time on two screens at home, we simply know too much about the conflicts of the world.
